Senate leader, Ahmed Ibrahim Lawan, has donated Ramadan items to people in his constituency through his Youth Empowerment Foundation (SAIL). The items include 2,000 bags of rice; 2,700 bags of Sugar; 1,500 bags of Millet and 500 cartons of vegetable oil. The Executive Officer of the SAIL foundation, Habu M Kaku, told newsmen in Damaturu that the donation was an annual gift by the Senate leader to cushion the suffering of people in the Holy Month of Ramadan. He said most part of the food items have been distributed to the beneficiaries, while others currently on dispatch. He called on the beneficiaries pray for peace and tranquillity to rein in Yobe, Northeast and the entire country